This paper deals with the problem of mapping between different modalities of data, which is a common theme in several sub-fields of computer science. The use of convolutional neural networks and skip-gram architecture suggests that the paper is likely to be related to natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV), which are covered by the cs.CL and cs.CV sub-categories respectively. The paper also introduces a simplified training objective for learning multimodal embeddings, which is a machine learning task, suggesting that it could be relevant to the cs.LG sub-category. The use of embeddings and word similarity benchmarks further suggests that the paper could be related to information retrieval (IR) and artificial intelligence (AI), which are covered by the cs.IR and cs.AI sub-categories respectively.
